</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0083-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0083-fn-0001">1</a>
	
   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0073" class="document">Council of War, this date</a>. GW enclosed a copy of the minutes in this letter (<span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Connecticut State Library, Hartford ]">Ct</span>: Trumbull Papers).</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0083-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0083-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>For GWs efforts to extend the service of the Massachusetts militia to the end of January, see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0041" class="document">GW to the Massachusetts Council, 10 Jan. 1776.</a></p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0083-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0083-fn-0003">3</a>

   <p>The letter-book copy in <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span> reads to be in readiness to act.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0083-fn-0004-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0083-fn-0004">4</a>

   <p>This enclosure has not been identified.</p>

